column5: I got out on simcoe for the first time this season yesterday and today and we slayed some jumbos! Picked up 22 over 10" today alone.  I thought yall might like this little piggy though. My second biggest perch ever and a pb for simcoe
That's a beauty for sure. Well done. Hopefully I'll have   a mess of them to clean tomorrow night when I get home.
jumbo on steroids!  sounds like a fun couple days
Thanks fellas,im normally a pike guy but this big that many ill play panfisher for a while ?
Ya, that's a brute!  We fished Simcoe for 2 hour.  Left with 23 eaters.  And 2 over 14".  Decent start to the season.
Nice perch for sure!  I can't wait to get out.  The cold temps & high winds have kept me house bound.
